PART: Recipes
NAME: Recipes
STATUS: draft

DATA: Recipe Book
MARKER: recipe_book
INTENT: holds all recipes and their details
TAGS: #time
---
The app holds a collection of recipes. Each recipe has a title, ingredients, instructions, cooking time, and a rating.

STRUCTURE: Recipe List Screen
MARKER: recipe_list_screen
INTENT: the main screen showing all recipes
TAGS: #list, #search
---
The screen has a header with the app name, a scrollable list of recipe cards, and a search bar at the top.

WHEN: Search Recipe
MARKER: search_recipe
INTENT: user searches for a recipe by title
TAGS: #card, #list, #search, #user
---
When the user types in the search bar, the list of recipes filters to show only those with titles containing the search term. The user can tap on a recipe card to view its details.

WHEN: Add Recipe
MARKER: add_recipe
INTENT: user adds a new recipe
TAGS: #form, #list, #time, #user
---
When the user taps the add button, a form appears. The user fills in the recipe title, ingredients, instructions, cooking time, and rating. The new recipe appears at the top of the list.

ASSERT: Recipe Title
MARKER: recipe_title
INTENT: validation for recipe title
---
A recipe title cannot be empty.

SURFACE: Recipe Card
MARKER: recipe_card
INTENT: labels and button names for recipe cards
TAGS: #card
---
The recipe card displays the title, a brief description, and a "View Details" button. The empty state reads "No recipes yet — add one above".